I wanted to share the attached powerpoint presentation that we put together for CardConnect senior
management, I thought there might be some things in here of interest.

- We found CardConnect's approach to the ISV channel truly unique and differentiated in the market.
- CardConnect has the broadest and deepest set of ISV integrations of any company we are aware of.
- We found that CardConnect followed through on their "promise" to help ISVs get more merchants and
  grow (as opposed to simply converting an ISV's portfolio, as many acquirers would do/have done)
- We heard consistent feedback that your onboarding support and expertise, particularly in the Enterprise
  area, exceeded anything ISVs had experienced elsewhere.
- CardConnect is not afraid of taking on the more complex integrations that others would shy away from.
- We performed an analysis of the ISV portfolios that had been converted to CardConnect from other
  acquirers and found significant volume uplift as a result of being on CardConnect as opposed to the
  former acquirer (please see page 7)

eConduit:

EXHIBIT
38

Our eConduit platform offers a creative approach to solving complex integration problems. Our web service methods include
both SOAP and RESTful services, allowing for the greatest flexibility in building connections between systems.

The complexities of integrating disparate systems call for solutions without limitations. eConduit has no restrictions on the
amount of data that can pass through which allows us to solve and support enterprise level integrations.

Gateway features:
•	 Reporting and management tool
